        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-62" edge="1" parent="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-48" source="L6GTwkRNaXk8acRgHraN-38" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;entryX=0.965;entryY=0.513;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;entryPerimeter=0;" target="nWNinx9GMLmJqjKlsHqI-1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-63" edge="1" parent="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-48" source="L6GTwkRNaXk8acRgHraN-38" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;entryX=-0.04;entryY=0.498;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;entryPerimeter=0;" target="L6GTwkRNaXk8acRgHraN-37">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-50" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;fontSize=14;" value="&lt;p data-start=&quot;134&quot; data-end=&quot;249&quot;&gt;Atualmente, o &lt;strong data-start=&quot;148&quot; data-end=&quot;197&quot;&gt;IICS (Informatica Intelligent Cloud Services)&lt;/strong&gt; é responsável por executar os jobs de integração.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;251&quot; data-end=&quot;263&quot;&gt;Ele realiza:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-start=&quot;264&quot; data-end=&quot;433&quot;&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;264&quot; data-end=&quot;330&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;266&quot; data-end=&quot;330&quot;&gt;Leitura e escrita diretamente no &lt;strong data-start=&quot;299&quot; data-end=&quot;330&quot;&gt;banco de dados do Data Lake&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;331&quot; data-end=&quot;433&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;333&quot; data-end=&quot;433&quot;&gt;Integração bidirecional com o &lt;strong data-start=&quot;363&quot; data-end=&quot;377&quot;&gt;Salesforce&lt;/strong&gt;, lendo e escrevendo dados conforme as regras de negócio&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;435&quot; data-end=&quot;558&quot;&gt;Ou seja, o IICS atua como camada central de orquestração e transformação, conectando diretamente o Data Lake ao Salesforce.&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="190" width="710" x="930" y="110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-51" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=13;" value="&lt;p data-start=&quot;101&quot; data-end=&quot;179&quot;&gt;O &lt;strong data-start=&quot;103&quot; data-end=&quot;117&quot;&gt;Databricks&lt;/strong&gt; passa a ser responsável pela execução do job de integração.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;181&quot; data-end=&quot;193&quot;&gt;Ele realiza:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-start=&quot;194&quot; data-end=&quot;363&quot;&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;194&quot; data-end=&quot;260&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;196&quot; data-end=&quot;260&quot;&gt;Leitura e escrita diretamente no &lt;strong data-start=&quot;229&quot; data-end=&quot;260&quot;&gt;banco de dados do Data Lake&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;261&quot; data-end=&quot;363&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;263&quot; data-end=&quot;363&quot;&gt;Integração bidirecional com o &lt;strong data-start=&quot;293&quot; data-end=&quot;307&quot;&gt;Salesforce&lt;/strong&gt;, lendo e escrevendo dados conforme as regras de negócio&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;365&quot; data-end=&quot;518&quot;&gt;Nesse modelo, o Databricks assume a orquestração e processamento da integração, substituindo o IICS como camada central entre o Data Lake e o Salesforce.&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="190" width="740" x="1050" y="445" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-52" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=13;" value="&lt;p data-start=&quot;97&quot; data-end=&quot;224&quot;&gt;Caso não seja viável realizar leitura e escrita diretamente no banco do Data Lake, a integração ocorrerá de forma intermediada.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;226&quot; data-end=&quot;239&quot;&gt;Neste modelo:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-start=&quot;240&quot; data-end=&quot;469&quot;&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;240&quot; data-end=&quot;301&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;242&quot; data-end=&quot;301&quot;&gt;O &lt;strong data-start=&quot;244&quot; data-end=&quot;258&quot;&gt;Databricks&lt;/strong&gt; executa o processamento e prepara os dados&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;302&quot; data-end=&quot;387&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;304&quot; data-end=&quot;387&quot;&gt;A integração com o banco do &lt;strong data-start=&quot;332&quot; data-end=&quot;345&quot;&gt;Data Lake&lt;/strong&gt; é realizada via &lt;strong data-start=&quot;362&quot; data-end=&quot;387&quot;&gt;Informatica Developer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;388&quot; data-end=&quot;469&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;390&quot; data-end=&quot;469&quot;&gt;O Informatica Developer passa a ser responsável pela leitura e escrita no banco&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;471&quot; data-end=&quot;616&quot;&gt;Assim, o Databricks concentra o processamento e regras de negócio, enquanto o Informatica Developer atua como camada de acesso ao banco de dados.&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="960" x="1230" y="780" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-53" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=13;" value="&lt;p data-start=&quot;122&quot; data-end=&quot;210&quot;&gt;Nesta alternativa, é adicionada uma camada de transferência via &lt;strong data-start=&quot;186&quot; data-end=&quot;209&quot;&gt;RVS (File Transfer)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;212&quot; data-end=&quot;225&quot;&gt;Neste modelo:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-start=&quot;226&quot; data-end=&quot;450&quot;&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;226&quot; data-end=&quot;297&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;228&quot; data-end=&quot;297&quot;&gt;O &lt;strong data-start=&quot;230&quot; data-end=&quot;244&quot;&gt;Databricks&lt;/strong&gt; entrega e recebe arquivos por meio do &lt;strong data-start=&quot;283&quot; data-end=&quot;297&quot;&gt;RVS Brasil&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;298&quot; data-end=&quot;375&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;300&quot; data-end=&quot;375&quot;&gt;O &lt;strong data-start=&quot;302&quot; data-end=&quot;327&quot;&gt;Informatica Developer&lt;/strong&gt; envia e recebe arquivos via &lt;strong data-start=&quot;356&quot; data-end=&quot;375&quot;&gt;RVS Informatica&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;376&quot; data-end=&quot;450&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;378&quot; data-end=&quot;450&quot;&gt;A transferência de dados ocorre entre os dois ambientes através dos RVSs&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;452&quot; data-end=&quot;653&quot;&gt;Assim, o Databricks e o Informatica Developer não se comunicam diretamente. A integração passa a ser baseada em troca de arquivos, com os RVSs responsáveis pela transferência segura entre os ambientes.&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="210" width="830" x="1450" y="1111" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-54" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=13;" value="&lt;p data-start=&quot;161&quot; data-end=&quot;229&quot;&gt;Neste cenário, o objetivo é realizar a &lt;strong data-start=&quot;200&quot; data-end=&quot;228&quot;&gt;migração total dos dados&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;231&quot; data-end=&quot;313&quot;&gt;O &lt;strong data-start=&quot;233&quot; data-end=&quot;247&quot;&gt;Databricks&lt;/strong&gt; passa a acessar diretamente toda a base do Data Lake, realizando:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-start=&quot;314&quot; data-end=&quot;458&quot;&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;314&quot; data-end=&quot;350&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;316&quot; data-end=&quot;350&quot;&gt;Leitura direta dos dados na origem&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;351&quot; data-end=&quot;411&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;353&quot; data-end=&quot;411&quot;&gt;Processamento e transformação conforme as regras definidas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;412&quot; data-end=&quot;458&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;414&quot; data-end=&quot;458&quot;&gt;Migração integral para o ambiente de destino&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;460&quot; data-end=&quot;611&quot;&gt;Nesse modelo, o Databricks atua como motor central da migração, eliminando camadas intermediárias e realizando o processo de forma direta e controlada.&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="210" width="930" x="890" y="1880" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-55" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=13;" value="&lt;p data-start=&quot;119&quot; data-end=&quot;209&quot;&gt;Neste cenário, a migração ocorre de forma desacoplada por meio de arquivos intermediários.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;211&quot; data-end=&quot;272&quot;&gt;O &lt;strong data-start=&quot;213&quot; data-end=&quot;238&quot;&gt;Informatica Developer&lt;/strong&gt;, através de um novo job, realiza:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-start=&quot;273&quot; data-end=&quot;454&quot;&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;273&quot; data-end=&quot;328&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;275&quot; data-end=&quot;328&quot;&gt;Leitura dos dados diretamente das tabelas de origem&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;329&quot; data-end=&quot;389&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;331&quot; data-end=&quot;389&quot;&gt;Transformação e geração dos dados no formato &lt;strong data-start=&quot;376&quot; data-end=&quot;387&quot;&gt;Parquet&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;390&quot; data-end=&quot;454&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;392&quot; data-end=&quot;454&quot;&gt;Entrega dos arquivos em um bucket &lt;strong data-start=&quot;426&quot; data-end=&quot;452&quot;&gt;Amazon S3 (AWS Brasil)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;456&quot; data-end=&quot;486&quot;&gt;O &lt;strong data-start=&quot;458&quot; data-end=&quot;472&quot;&gt;Databricks&lt;/strong&gt;, por sua vez:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-start=&quot;487&quot; data-end=&quot;595&quot;&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;487&quot; data-end=&quot;534&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;489&quot; data-end=&quot;534&quot;&gt;Realiza a leitura direta dos arquivos no S3&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-start=&quot;535&quot; data-end=&quot;595&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;537&quot; data-end=&quot;595&quot;&gt;Executa o processamento e a carga no ambiente de destino&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;597&quot; data-end=&quot;755&quot;&gt;Nesse modelo, o S3 atua como camada intermediária de armazenamento, promovendo desacoplamento entre os sistemas e maior controle sobre o processo de migração.&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="300" width="1020" x="950" y="2250" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-64" edge="1" parent="1" source="nWNinx9GMLmJqjKlsHqI-1" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;entryX=1;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;entryPerimeter=0;" target="U01bOSqINZ_HKZLMmUMp-1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
